    description: 'The Winter War began on November 30, 1939, when the Soviet Union attacked Finland after Finland refused to cede strategic territory near Leningrad. Despite massive numerical superiority, the Red Army suffered catastrophic initial losses against Finnish defenders using superior tactics in the frozen forests of the Karelian Isthmus. After three months of fierce fighting, Finland signed the Moscow Peace Treaty, ceding roughly 11% of its territory but preserving its independence.',
