    description: 'Operation Weserübung on April 9, 1940 saw Germany launch simultaneous invasions of Denmark and Norway to secure vital iron ore supply routes from Sweden and preempt a planned Allied occupation. Denmark capitulated within hours, while Norway mounted fierce resistance supported by British and French expeditionary forces. Norway fell by early June 1940 after the Allies withdrew, providing Germany with strategic Atlantic coastline for naval and air operations.',
